image.text: A near-stationary trough in the east is triggering thunderstorms from the NSW ranges to western QLD. A low is generating strong showery winds in TAS. A high in the Bight is directing dry, gusty southeasterlies across VIC and SA. A trough in WA is causing storms in the south.The northern jet is mostly zonal across southern WA and SA, and isn't much affecting the weather. The polar jet is directing a cold front across the southeast, allowing colder air to reach TAS and the VIC coastline.
